FBIS4-28878 "dreas114_c_94027" FBIS-EAS-94-114 Daily Report 10 Jun 1994 North Korea Philippine President Remarks on Nuclear Issue Philippine President Remarks on Nuclear Issue SK1006053194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0443 GMT 10 Jun 94 SK1006053194 Pyongyang KCNA English BFN ["`actions Against North Korea Could Bring the Korean Peninsula Down the Road to Conflict': Philippine President" -- KCNA headline] [Text] Pyongyang, June 10 (KCNA) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos at his weekly press conference on June 8 called for the avoidance of actions against North Korea that might provoke a confrontation, which he said in turn could bring the region down the road to conflict, according to a XINHUA report. The president reiterated the Philippine policy on North Korea's "nuclear issue" that has been to urge patient consultation and creative diplomacy in the search for a solution. He said "the Philippines hope that a peaceful solution could still be found to resolve the issue."
